{"TopicId":219269,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Center of mass indicator does not get updated when modifying fuel amount values in fuel tanks [or at all until toggling symmetry or picking up craft]","CreatedByName":"Moredice","CreatedById":229539,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-03T22:28:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Moredice","CreatedById":229539,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-03T22:28:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.4 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 22H2 (build 19045.3324) | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 9 5950X | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Asus ROG Strix GeForce 1080 Ti OC 11gb | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32 gb 3200MHz DDR4\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, while \u0022Center of Mass\u0022 indication is enabled, the indicator does not move accordingly as fuel amount is being modified in fuel tanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne needs to disable and enable the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator again, pick up another part from the part picker\u00A0(does not need to be attached to the craft) or detach and reattach any part on the craft to update the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s position.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHow to reproduce:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nPlace two fuel tanks connected with one another.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nEnable the \u0022Center of Mass\u0022 indicator.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nRight click one tank and change its fuel contents to zero.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nObserve that the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E did not move.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nEither disable and enable \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E indication again, select a new part from the part picker or detach and reattach one of the fuel tanks.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nObserve that the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E did in fact move.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe screenshot illustrates the issue, the video demonstrates the issue, the craft file contains simply the two fuel tanks from step 1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220230904001830_1.jpg.8609b0e132d21005d59a96874cfd6155.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_09/20230904001830_1.jpg.8609b0e132d21005d59a96874cfd6155.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=Window04-09-202300-20-22.mp4\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5B4vu5qWkhqEp17AitjXG2s9jCXfoHe97YDxRM51gFVWPWX51CX3SliZJUTS9V3N7%2BD0609NRud/y0PXW49mmEit6Dzr3EKRNQVumWxt8UuHrQ%5D%5B40bb2418a583597f58307622%5D%5B64439e1a2cf407cc13d63ca482c126d6%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EWindow04-09-202300-20-22.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=fuel_tanks.json\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5BhjB/uWc54Xzom9fOXYC38djULIVfKceNwVYYww//KMEqwuozF8%2BbftMcvLuKE4RW55bqiwSDopXvpj/PoDls2g==%5D%5B277396f49eaecbef588f0f39%5D%5B4adbd5e88df53dfc50022081d5e55b70%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Efuel_tanks.json\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-09-05T03:54:17Z\u0022 title=\u002209/05/2023 03:54  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Sep 5\u0022\u003ESeptember 5, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"spaceman42069","CreatedById":230465,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-04T16:44:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.4 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Win 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0ryzen9 7950X | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0RTX 4080 16GB | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003EDDR5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDescription:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAs per the title: Center of Mass widget does not update until you toggle it off and on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-09-04T21:36:23Z\u0022 title=\u002209/04/2023 09:3